cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.CY 

This paper deals with privacy protection in mobile applications, which is a common concern in the field of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a method to maximize mobile crowd's future location coverage, which involves data analysis and optimization (cs.SI). The use of frequently visited locations and obfuscation techniques also suggests a connection to databases (cs.DB). The paper also presents experimental results, which may fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the topic of location privacy protection may also be relevant to the sub-category of cyber-physical systems (cs.CY).
